post_cb({"bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_2792028_2792103_1": {"length": 12, "quality": 0.631578947368421, "section_id": 3298}}, "n3337": {"so_2792028_2792103_1": {"length": 12, "quality": 0.631578947368421, "section_id": 3168}}}, "2792103": {"LastActivityDate": "2010-05-07T22:52:29.480", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<p>It shouldn't be supported <a href=\"http://connect.microsoft.com/VisualStudio/feedback/details/533464/the-initializer-list-header-in-the-vc10-release-candidate\" rel=\"noreferrer\">at all</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_2792028_2792103_0\">[...] the C++0x Core Language feature of initializer lists and the associated Standard Library changes weren't implemented in VC10.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>The error message refers to the pre-C++0x feature of aggregate initialization, which allows the initialization of certain user-defined types by using curly braces:</p>\n<pre><code>struct pair { int first; char second; };\npair p = { 0, 'c' };\n</code></pre>\n<p>Aggregates are defined in <em>\u00a78.5.1</em>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_2792028_2792103_1\">An aggregate is an array or a class (clause 9) with no user-declared constructors (12.1), no private or protected non-static data members (clause 11), no base classes (clause 10), and no virtual functions (10.3).  </p>\n<p id=\"so_2792028_2792103_2\">When an aggregate is initialized the initializer can contain an initializer-clause consisting of a brace- enclosed, comma-separated list of initializer-clauses for the members of the aggregate, written in increasing subscript or member order. If the aggregate contains subaggregates, this rule applies recursively to the members of the subaggregate. </p>\n</blockquote>\n", "CreationDate": "2010-05-07T22:40:16.913", "LastEditDate": "2010-05-07T22:52:29.480", "ParentId": "2792028", "Id": "2792103", "LastEditorUserId": "4304", "PostTypeId": "2", "Score": "34", "OwnerUserId": "168225"}, "2792028": {"CreationDate": "2010-05-07T22:21:22.033", "ViewCount": "9223", "FavoriteCount": "2", "Id": "2792028", "AcceptedAnswerId": "2792103", "Score": "16", "Title": "initializer_list not working in VC10", "LastEditorUserId": "168225", "CommentCount": "1", "Body": "<p>i wrote this program in VC++ 2010:</p>\n<pre><code>class class1\n{\npublic:\n class1 (initializer_list&lt;int&gt; a){};\n int foo;\n float Bar;\n};\nvoid main()\n{\n class1 c = {2,3};\n getchar();\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>but i get this errors when i compile project:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_2792028_2792028_0\">Error 1 error C2552: 'c' :\n  non-aggregates cannot be initialized\n  with initializer\n  list c:\\users\\pswin\\documents\\visual\n  studio\n  2010\\projects\\test_c++0x\\test_c++0x\\main.cpp 27</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>and </p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_2792028_2792028_1\">2 IntelliSense: initialization with\n  '{...}' is not allowed for object of\n  type\n  \"class1\" c:\\users\\pswin\\documents\\visual\n  studio\n  2010\\projects\\test_c++0x\\test_c++0x\\main.cpp 27</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>what is the problem?</p>\n", "Tags": "<c++><visual-c++><c++11><initializer-list><visual-c++-2010>", "LastEditDate": "2010-05-08T00:46:35.273", "LastActivityDate": "2010-05-08T00:46:35.273", "PostTypeId": "1", "AnswerCount": "1", "OwnerUserId": "335870"}});